        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 24 at 3:45PM CDT by NWS Lake Charles LA</headline>
        <description>At 345 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Hineston, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Glenmora, Hineston, Lecompte, Leander, Sieper, Otis, Elmer,
Calcasieu, Woodworth, Forest Hill, and Mcnary.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
